The paper discusses the use of learning classifier systems, which are a type of machine learning algorithm falling under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of dynamical system representations also suggests a connection to the categories of neural and evolutionary computation (cs.NE) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents results from solving test problems, indicating a potential connection to the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
